HOUSE BILL No. 1212
_____
DIGEST OF INTRODUCED BILL
Citations Affected: IC 12-15-1.3-27.
Synopsis: Medicaid coverage for health related social needs. Requires
the office of the secretary of family and social services to apply, not
later than October 1, 2026, for approval of a Section 1115 Medicaid
demonstration waiver to provide coverage for health related social
needs.
Effective: July 1, 2026.
Moed
January 5, 2026, read first time and referred to Committee on Public Health.
2026 IN 1212—LS 6513/DI 147

Introduced
Second Regular Session of the 124th General Assembly (2026)
PRINTING CODE. Amendments: Whenever an existing statute (or a section of the Indiana
Constitution) is being amended, the text of the existing provision will appear in this style type,
additions will appear in this style type, and deletions will appear in this style type.
Additions: Whenever a new statutory provision is being enacted (or a new constitutional
provision adopted), the text of the new provision will appear in this style type. Also, the
word NEW will appear in that style type in the introductory clause of each SECTION that adds
a new provision to the Indiana Code or the Indiana Constitution.
Conflict reconciliation: Text in a statute in this style type or this style type reconciles conflicts
between statutes enacted by the 2025 Regular Session of the General Assembly.
HOUSE BILL No. 1212
A BILL FOR AN ACT to amend the Indiana Code concerning
human services.
Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the State of Indiana:
1 SECTION 1. IC 12-15-1.3-27 IS ADDED TO THE INDIANA
2 CODE AS A NEW SECTION TO READ AS FOLLOWS
3 [EFFECTIVE JULY 1, 2026]: Sec. 27. (a) As used in this section,
4 "health related social needs" means an individual's unmet, adverse
5 social conditions that contribute to poor health outcomes, such as
6 food insecurity, housing instability, unemployment, or lack of
7 transportation.
8 (b) Not later than October 1, 2026, the office of the secretary
9 shall apply to the United States Department of Health and Human
10 Services for approval of a Section 1115 Medicaid demonstration
11 waiver to provide Medicaid coverage for health related social
12 needs, including coverage for the following:
13 (1) Housing supports.
14 (2) Nutrition supports.
15 (3) Any other health related social needs services identified by
16 the office of the secretary.
